This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and semantic analysis of news statements. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning algorithms to detect fake news. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the retrieval and analysis of information from a dataset. It could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of frameworks for machine learning algorithms. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the societal impact of fake news and the need for explainable AI systems.
